This puppet module installs apache for RHEL, starts the service and creates a basic static webpage from an erb template.
If the uninstall => true argument is passed in the command, it will stop the service, purge httpd from the system and remove the index.html file.
On the system, the module is stored just below the root directory, if stored anywhere else, the syntax of the command/files will have to be altered.

The command used is.
puppet apply --modulepath=/root/ -e "class {'apachehost' : uninstall => false}"
or if you want to uninstall,
puppet apply --modulepath=/root/ -e "class {'apachehost' : uninstall => true}"
